I am writing reviews for all the jerk chicken spots in the area. This is my 4th one thus far. This place is not close to my house, so it may be the only time I ever come here, but I was impressed by all accounts.  To  begin, I always order the same thing, a dark chicken dinner. Everything was on point and tasted marvelous. The Chicken was juicy and the cabbage was perfect. I only recieved one plantain but never the less it was very good. The meal came out piping hot and stayed heated the entire ride home. I even payed extra for some mac and chese and it was well worth the money. This place was pretty pricy, but I only judge after I ate the meal, and I did not mind paying the extra dollars for the quality.  Everbody in there was very nice and I could tell they took pride in their work. The ambaniance had a very exciting carriban vibe and they made you feel welcome. Only thing that sucks about this place is they are only located in the city limits of Chicago. A couple of new suburb locatations would be appreciated and lucrative.
